---
id: org.dxos.plugin.generator
name: GeneratorPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

AI-driven media generation plugin for `DXOS` Composer.
Generates short videos and audio clips from a markdown text prompt via a
pluggable `GenerationProvider`. The initial provider implementation calls the
HeyGen API; the abstraction is intentionally provider-agnostic so additional
back-ends (e.g. Veo, Sora, ElevenLabs) can be added without changing the
`Generation` data model or the article surface.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## Types

```mdl
type MediaKind
  literals: video | audio
```

```mdl
type Generation
  desc: |
    A single media-generation artefact. The `prompt` is a ref to a markdown
    Text object that the user edits via the article. The `url` is populated
    by the GenerationProvider on successful completion. `avatarId` and
    `voiceId` are provider-agnostic identifiers passed through to the
    underlying service when applicable.
  fields:
    name?: string
    type: MediaKind
    avatarId?: string             # provider-specific avatar / character id
    voiceId?: string              # provider-specific voice id
    prompt: Ref<Text>             # markdown source
    url?: string                  # remote artefact URL (video / audio)
```

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: Plugin-level settings persisted to local KVS.
  fields:
    apiKey?: string               # provider API key
```

```mdl
type GenerateInput
  fields:
    type: MediaKind
    prompt: string
    avatarId?: string             # forwarded to providers that use one
    voiceId?: string              # forwarded to providers that use one
```

```mdl
type GenerateResult
  fields:
    url: string
```

```mdl
type GenerationOption
  desc: An identified avatar or voice. `id` is the value assigned to Generation.avatarId / Generation.voiceId; `name` is a human-readable label suitable for a picker.
  fields:
    id: string
    name: string
```

## Services

```mdl
service GenerationProvider
  desc: |
    Abstract media generation back-end. Implementations adapt remote
    providers (HeyGen, Veo, Sora, ElevenLabs) to a single uniform shape.
    Providers that don't model avatars or voices return an empty list.
  ops:
    generate(input: GenerateInput) → GenerateResult
    listAvatars() → GenerationOption[]
    listVoices() → GenerationOption[]
  errors:
    MissingApiKey: provider requires an API key and none is configured
    ProviderFailure: upstream provider returned an error
    UnsupportedKind: provider does not support the requested MediaKind
```

```mdl
service HeyGenProvider
  desc: HeyGen video generation adapter — implements GenerationProvider.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    generate(input: GenerateInput) → GenerateResult
    listAvatars() → GenerationOption[]
    listVoices() → GenerationOption[]
  note: |
    `generate` calls POST https://api.heygen.com/v2/video/generate then polls
    GET https://api.heygen.com/v1/video_status.get until status === 'completed'
    (or 'failed'). `listAvatars` merges avatars and talking-photos returned by
    GET /v2/avatars. `listVoices` maps GET /v2/voices, suffixing the label
    with language and gender when present.
```

## Components

```mdl
component GenerationArticle
  desc: Main surface for a Generation object.
  props:
    subject: Generation
  state:
    busy: boolean
    error?: string
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  actions:
    generate()                    # invokes GenerationProvider.generate
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar: ▶ Generate]       │
    ├─────────────────────────────┤
    │ Prompt editor (markdown)    │
    │                             │
    │ ─────────────────────────── │
    │ <video|audio src=url />     │
    └─────────────────────────────┘
```

## Operations

```mdl
op generate
  desc: Generate media for a Generation object using the active provider.
  input:
    generation: Generation
  output: Generation              # mutated with url set
  errors:
    MissingApiKey: settings.apiKey is undefined or empty
    ProviderFailure: provider rejected the request
  effects: [echo:write, http]
  requires: [GenerationProvider]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Create Generation

  req F-1.1: User can create a `Generation` object from the space menu.
  req F-1.2: New `Generation` defaults `type` to 'video' and creates an empty markdown prompt.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Edit Prompt

  req F-2.1:
    when: article is shown for a Generation
    then: the markdown prompt text is editable inline
  req F-2.2:
    when: prompt text changes
    then: changes persist via the linked Text ref and replicate to other peers
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Generate Media

  req F-3.1: Toolbar exposes a single Generate button.
  req F-3.2:
    when: user clicks Generate and settings.apiKey is empty
    then: surface an error pointing the user to the Settings panel
  req F-3.3:
    when: user clicks Generate with a valid apiKey
    then: GenerationProvider.generate is invoked with { type, prompt }
  req F-3.4:
    when: provider returns success
    then: Generation.url is set; UI shows the new media in a player
  req F-3.5:
    when: provider fails
    then: error is surfaced in the article statusbar; Generation.url unchanged
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Playback

  req F-4.1:
    when: Generation.url is set and type === 'video'
    then: a `<video controls>` element renders below the prompt editor
  req F-4.2:
    when: Generation.url is set and type === 'audio'
    then: an `<audio controls>` element renders below the prompt editor
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Provider Settings

  req F-5.1: Plugin Settings panel exposes an `API key` input.
  req F-5.2: Setting is persisted to local KVS, scoped to `meta.id`.
  req F-5.3: The Generate flow reads `apiKey` reactively — toggling it
             enables/disables the toolbar button without reload.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Default Generation
  given: user creates a new Generation
  then:
    - Generation.type === 'video'
    - Generation.prompt is a Ref<Text> whose content === ''
    - Generation.url is undefined
```

```mdl
test T-2: Missing API key
  given: settings.apiKey is unset
  when: user clicks Generate
  then:
    - MissingApiKey error surfaced
    - Generation.url unchanged
```

```mdl
test T-3: Successful video generation
  given: settings.apiKey is set, Generation.type === 'video', prompt is non-empty
  when: user clicks Generate
  then:
    - GenerationProvider.generate called with the prompt's resolved content
    - Generation.url set to the returned URL
    - `<video>` element renders with the URL as src
```

```mdl
test T-4: Audio generation
  given: settings.apiKey is set, Generation.type === 'audio'
  when: user clicks Generate
  then:
    - Generation.url set
    - `<audio>` element renders with the URL as src
```
